WEBVTT

00:01.280 --> 00:08.420
Dominoes, Level 1. The wrong trousers. Chapter 1. Happy birthday,

00:08.500 --> 00:09.140
Chuck.

00:11.540 --> 00:15.200
It was early in the morning on Wednesday the 12th.

00:15.860 --> 00:18.080
Gromit the dog sat at the table in the

00:18.080 --> 00:21.720
kitchen of the little house at 62 West Wallaby Street

00:21.720 --> 00:25.880
and made breakfast. Suddenly he remembered

00:25.880 --> 00:29.660
something. He got up from the table and went to

00:29.660 --> 00:31.420
look at the calendar near the door.

00:32.540 --> 00:37.340
Wednesday the 12th was his birthday. There it was on

00:37.340 --> 00:38.800
the calendar in blue pen.

00:39.720 --> 00:44.740
Gromit's birthday. Gromit took a pen and put a big

00:44.740 --> 00:47.160
blue X through the number 12.

00:48.480 --> 00:53.140
It's my birthday today and my friend Wallace is sleeping,

00:53.800 --> 00:56.420
he thought, and he felt sad.

00:57.480 --> 01:02.040
Wallace wasn't a dog. He was a man and Gromit

01:02.040 --> 01:05.540
lived with him at 62 West Wallaby Street.

01:06.840 --> 01:10.760
Gromit looked at his watch. It was nine o'clock.

01:11.740 --> 01:14.680
Just then he heard a noise at the front door.

01:15.540 --> 01:21.580
There. That's the postman, he thought. Perhaps I'm going to

01:21.580 --> 01:23.680
get some birthday cards this morning.

01:24.220 --> 01:29.100
Let's go and see. There were six letters by the

01:29.100 --> 01:32.260
front door when Gromit arrived there and he looked

01:32.260 --> 01:35.740
at all of them carefully. Most of them were letters

01:35.740 --> 01:39.440
for Wallace, letters in brown envelopes asking

01:39.440 --> 01:44.080
for money. But there was one envelope, a green one,

01:44.480 --> 01:48.180
for Gromit. With all six letters in his mouth,

01:48.840 --> 01:53.740
Gromit ran back to the kitchen. Suddenly a toy train

01:53.740 --> 01:57.040
shot out in front of him. He stopped for a

01:57.040 --> 02:00.940
minute. The train went past and then he ran on

02:00.940 --> 02:05.120
back to the breakfast table. There were lots of

02:05.120 --> 02:09.240
different machines in Wallace and Gromit's house in West Wallaby

02:09.240 --> 02:09.580
Street.

02:10.980 --> 02:14.720
Back in the kitchen, Gromit sat down at the table

02:14.720 --> 02:16.440
and opened the green envelope.

02:17.140 --> 02:20.400
It was a birthday card with a picture of a

02:20.400 --> 02:23.460
smiling dog on the front and when he opened it,

02:23.700 --> 02:28.860
it played, happy birthday to you. Gromit put the card

02:28.860 --> 02:31.500
on the table and looked at it sadly.

02:31.500 --> 02:39.000
Only one birthday card on his birthday. Just then, a

02:39.000 --> 02:42.100
red light over his head began to go on and

02:42.100 --> 02:42.480
off.

02:43.540 --> 02:48.320
Upstairs Wallace was in bed. There was a red button

02:48.320 --> 02:52.660
next to his bed. It said breakfast on it.

02:53.620 --> 02:58.120
Wallace hit it again and again. Breakfast said the red

02:58.120 --> 03:00.020
light in the kitchen over Gromit's head.

03:01.500 --> 03:05.220
Down in the kitchen, Gromit moved a lever behind his

03:05.220 --> 03:08.720
chair. At once, up in Wallace's room,

03:09.520 --> 03:12.900
the head of the bed moved up. At the same

03:12.900 --> 03:16.260
time, a door opened in the floor at the foot

03:16.260 --> 03:16.820
of the bed.

03:17.640 --> 03:20.840
The table in the kitchen was right under this door.

03:21.740 --> 03:24.620
Suddenly, Wallace shot out of bed crying,

03:24.620 --> 03:30.020
Gromit! He shot down through the door in the floor

03:30.020 --> 03:31.460
and was soon downstairs,

03:32.420 --> 03:34.900
sitting in his chair at the kitchen table.

03:35.880 --> 03:40.560
Well, Gromit, my getting up in the morning machine worked

03:40.560 --> 03:43.680
well, said Wallace, and he began

03:43.680 --> 03:48.520
to eat his breakfast. But perhaps I can make it

03:48.520 --> 03:52.820
work better. I hit the chair very fast that time,

03:52.820 --> 03:57.900
oh! Cracking breakfast, Gromit! he went on.

03:58.960 --> 04:02.040
Gromit read his newspaper and said nothing.

04:03.020 --> 04:09.020
Any letters today? asked Wallace. Gromit gave him his letters.

04:10.220 --> 04:14.160
Wallace opened the first brown envelope and took out a

04:14.160 --> 04:17.100
very long letter asking him for lots of money.

04:18.020 --> 04:22.640
Oh, dear! said Wallace, looking at the long letter carefully.

04:23.540 --> 04:26.980
He looked at all the brown envelopes in his hand.

04:27.760 --> 04:31.360
We must be more careful with money, Gromit!

04:32.300 --> 04:36.220
A Gromit put his birthday card on the table. It

04:36.220 --> 04:39.040
played happy birthday slowly and sadly,

04:39.740 --> 04:42.980
but Wallace wasn't interested in birthday cards just then.

04:44.080 --> 04:47.760
Wallace went to look in his money box. There was

04:47.760 --> 04:49.580
only thirty pens in it.

04:51.440 --> 04:56.580
Look at that, he said, and those presents weren't cheap.

04:57.660 --> 05:00.240
He put his hand over his mouth and looked at

05:00.240 --> 05:03.920
Gromit. Oh, no! He didn't want Gromit to know

05:03.920 --> 05:08.720
about his presents just then. Gromit looked at Wallace and

05:08.720 --> 05:10.560
his ears went up excitedly.

05:11.160 --> 05:14.980
Perhaps I'm going to get something more for my birthday,

05:15.440 --> 05:16.120
he thought.

05:17.780 --> 05:24.220
Well, Gromit, what's on the 905 train? said Wallace. Oh,

05:24.540 --> 05:26.580
look! Here it comes now!

05:27.940 --> 05:32.000
Wallace's little toy train came through the kitchen door and

05:32.000 --> 05:33.400
shot past the table.

05:34.120 --> 05:36.880
Quickly, Wallace took a little present of it.

05:37.640 --> 05:41.200
What's this? He said, and he put the present on

05:41.200 --> 05:42.720
the table in front of Gromit.

05:43.420 --> 05:45.260
Happy birthday, Chuck!

05:46.700 --> 05:50.800
Gromit quickly opened his birthday present. It was a red

05:50.800 --> 05:52.320
dog collar and lead.

05:53.200 --> 05:58.100
You wanted a collar? said Wallace, laughing. Here, let's put

05:58.100 --> 05:58.640
it on you.

05:59.440 --> 06:02.100
Wallace helped Gromit to put on his collar.

06:03.060 --> 06:06.380
Now people can see you come from a good home,

06:06.800 --> 06:07.220
he said.

06:07.900 --> 06:11.340
But that isn't all. Come and look in here.

06:12.600 --> 06:17.360
Gromit went into the front room. Something stood there in

06:17.360 --> 06:19.980
the dark. A new machine, perhaps.

06:20.980 --> 06:24.120
It began to make a noise, and it came out

06:24.120 --> 06:27.160
from behind the door. It was a big,

06:28.040 --> 06:33.460
walking present. It walked nearer and nearer to Gromit on

06:33.460 --> 06:34.800
its two big legs.

06:35.780 --> 06:41.520
Gromit felt very afraid. Suddenly the thing stopped, and Gromit

06:41.520 --> 06:42.360
saw a small

06:42.360 --> 06:46.900
card on the front of it. To Gromit, love Wallace

06:46.900 --> 06:48.200
said the card.

06:49.080 --> 06:53.100
Because Gromit was afraid, in the end, Wallace opened this

06:53.100 --> 06:53.900
second present.

06:53.900 --> 06:59.460
But what was it? Green and black trousers?

07:00.760 --> 07:05.600
Yes, but they were trousers with blue buttons and red

07:05.600 --> 07:06.100
levers.

07:06.900 --> 07:11.300
Their techno trousers said Wallace.

07:20.120 --> 07:24.080
Chapter Two, Room for Rent

07:28.700 --> 07:33.620
I think you're going to like these techno trousers, Wallace

07:33.620 --> 07:34.020
said.

07:34.640 --> 07:37.800
He put one end of Gromit's new lead on his

07:37.800 --> 07:40.400
collar, and the other end on the trousers.

07:41.520 --> 07:45.200
Then he hit some blue buttons and moved some red

07:45.200 --> 07:45.520
levers.

07:46.420 --> 07:53.220
Time for a walk! Ten? No! Twenty minutes, he said.

07:53.800 --> 07:56.660
Now what's happening? Thought Gromit.

07:57.220 --> 08:01.740
Suddenly the techno trousers began walking out of the door,

08:02.100 --> 08:04.000
and Gromit, in his collar and

08:04.000 --> 08:08.820
lead, went sadly with them. Have a nice walk, Gromit!

08:09.540 --> 08:10.260
Wallace laughed.

08:10.260 --> 08:15.980
There was a sign in the park. All dogs on

08:15.980 --> 08:17.380
a lead, it said.

08:18.460 --> 08:22.400
But when Gromit arrived, he didn't have his new lead

08:22.400 --> 08:24.720
on. Where was it?

08:25.600 --> 08:30.380
On a toy dog! So in the end Gromit played

08:30.380 --> 08:33.720
happily in the park, and the techno trousers

08:33.720 --> 08:38.720
took the toy dog for a walk. At home, in

08:38.720 --> 08:40.740
62 West Wallaby Street,

08:41.440 --> 08:45.340
Wallace sat in the kitchen. He had all the letters

08:45.340 --> 08:48.260
asking for money on the table in front of him.

08:49.140 --> 08:53.960
It's no good. We need some more money, he said.

08:54.820 --> 08:58.020
He wrote out a sign and put it in the

08:58.020 --> 08:59.320
front window of the house.

09:00.480 --> 09:06.260
Spare room for rent, it said. Gromit saw the sign

09:06.260 --> 09:07.940
when he came back from the park.

09:10.140 --> 09:13.780
Later that day, Wallace and Gromit sat in the front

09:13.780 --> 09:14.200
room.

09:15.000 --> 09:19.960
Did you have a nice walk, Chuck? Asked Wallace. How

09:19.960 --> 09:21.220
were the techno trousers?

09:22.820 --> 09:28.620
Gromit looked at him sadly and said nothing. Suddenly they

09:28.620 --> 09:30.220
heard a ring at the front door.

09:31.140 --> 09:33.800
Oh, there's someone at the door, Gromit!

09:34.860 --> 09:38.540
Wallace quickly got up and went to open the front

09:38.540 --> 09:38.920
door.

09:39.960 --> 09:43.540
Gromit stayed in his chair, but his ears went up,

09:43.940 --> 09:46.220
and he listened carefully to everything

09:46.220 --> 09:47.760
through the open door.

09:48.660 --> 09:54.060
Are you here about the room? Asked Wallace. That's Gromit!

09:54.540 --> 09:55.100
Gromit!

09:57.400 --> 10:02.780
The next minute a penguin walked quietly into 62 West

10:02.780 --> 10:03.600
Wallaby Street,

10:04.220 --> 10:08.320
with a little black bag. He went upstairs with Wallace.

10:09.300 --> 10:15.220
I'm asking twenty pounds a week. That's with breakfast. Wallace

10:15.220 --> 10:16.360
said to the penguin.

10:16.920 --> 10:21.860
They walked past Gromit's room. It's cheap because it's a

10:21.860 --> 10:22.620
dark room,

10:23.340 --> 10:27.660
said Wallace, opening the door to the spare room. But

10:27.660 --> 10:29.260
we can soon make it nice.

10:30.400 --> 10:34.060
The penguin took one look at the dark and dirty

10:34.060 --> 10:37.240
spare room and ran into Gromit's room.

10:37.760 --> 10:42.480
No, wait a minute, said Wallace. You can't. But the

10:42.480 --> 10:44.540
penguin got up on Gromit's bed,

10:45.120 --> 10:49.880
opened his bag, sat back happily and began listening to the radio.

10:51.040 --> 11:00.480
Yes. Well, that's OK then, said Wallace slowly, and he left the penguin in Gromit's room,

11:00.480 --> 11:03.200
closed the door and went downstairs.

11:04.160 --> 11:09.440
With the penguin now in Gromit's room, Gromit moved into the spare room.

11:10.320 --> 11:15.520
It's OK, Gromit! We can soon make it nice, said Wallace.

11:16.800 --> 11:20.160
Of course, they had the techno trousers to help them.

11:21.120 --> 11:26.560
The penguin was very, very interested in those when he saw them.

11:27.360 --> 11:34.960
Gromit couldn't sleep in his bed in the spare room that night because he could hear the penguin's radio.

11:35.920 --> 11:40.080
He went downstairs, but he could hear the radio there, too.

11:41.280 --> 11:48.160
Angrily, he went upstairs again to speak to the penguin, but he couldn't open the door to his room.

11:48.960 --> 11:51.600
And there was no answer when he knocked on it.

11:52.480 --> 12:00.240
In the end, Gromit went out sadly into the garden, but he could hear the radio out there, too.

12:01.360 --> 12:05.040
Very late that night, the penguin arrived home.

12:05.760 --> 12:09.840
He went into the house, up to his room, and to bed.

12:11.120 --> 12:14.400
Then the radio stopped, and everything went quiet.

12:15.200 --> 12:21.920
In the garden, Gromit put his head in his hands, and cried quietly.

12:30.800 --> 12:34.880
Chapter Three, penguin that's grand!

12:35.040 --> 12:44.480
The next day, when Gromit went to the bathroom, there was someone in there.

12:45.200 --> 12:46.320
Gromit waited.

12:47.360 --> 12:48.720
Wallace walked past.

12:49.440 --> 12:50.960
Good morning, Gromit!

12:50.960 --> 12:53.760
He said happily, and he went down to breakfast.

12:54.880 --> 12:57.200
Then the penguin came out of the bathroom.

12:58.400 --> 13:02.960
Later, when Gromit sat down for breakfast, Wallace put his feet up.

13:03.840 --> 13:06.480
The penguin quickly brought his slippers to him.

13:07.440 --> 13:11.040
Thank you very much, penguin, that's grand!

13:11.040 --> 13:13.760
Said Wallace, putting his feet into the slippers.

13:14.880 --> 13:19.280
Gromit usually took Wallace's newspaper when it came in the morning,

13:19.280 --> 13:24.400
but now the penguin got to the front door and back with a newspaper before Gromit.

13:25.280 --> 13:26.960
Oh, what do you think of that, Gromit?

13:27.520 --> 13:28.320
Asked Wallace.

13:28.960 --> 13:31.200
Our new friends are great help!

13:31.760 --> 13:32.320
He laughed.

13:33.600 --> 13:39.360
Gromit looked at Wallace and the penguin, and he felt angrier and angrier.

13:40.800 --> 13:43.760
That evening Gromit went out into the garden again.

13:44.800 --> 13:51.040
Through the window he could see Wallace and the penguin eating and drinking happily in the

13:51.040 --> 13:51.600
back room.

13:52.480 --> 13:54.320
A more cheese, penguin?

13:54.880 --> 13:55.600
Asked Wallace.

13:56.400 --> 13:59.120
Gromit looked away, sadly.

13:59.840 --> 14:07.360
He went into his kennel and put two or three of his most important things into a red and white bag.

14:08.400 --> 14:14.960
Before he left he took an old photo of Wallace in his hands and looked at it for a minute or two.

14:15.920 --> 14:22.320
Then he put the photo down, put on his yellow coat and hat, put his bag on his back,

14:23.120 --> 14:25.200
and walked off into the rain.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.400
Good night, penguin!

14:28.880 --> 14:29.680
Sleep well!

14:30.480 --> 14:31.280
Called Wallace.

14:32.480 --> 14:39.360
Under the cold rain Gromit slowly walked away from his kennel, away from his home in west

14:39.360 --> 14:43.440
Wallaby Street and away from his old friend, Wallace.

14:45.360 --> 14:50.400
From the house the penguin watched Gromit go and was happy.

14:51.360 --> 14:55.840
Then he went off to find the techno trousers.

14:58.880 --> 15:04.720
The next morning Gromit got up early after a night sleeping in a bin in the street.

15:05.600 --> 15:10.320
At home in west Wallaby Street, Wallace was happy in his bed.

15:11.360 --> 15:13.280
He opened his eyes slowly.

15:14.080 --> 15:21.280
Just then the head of his bed moved up and the door opened in the floor at the foot of the bed.

15:22.160 --> 15:28.320
Wallace shot out of bed, threw the door in the floor and down into the kitchen.

15:29.200 --> 15:34.080
But this time he didn't land in his usual brown trousers.

15:34.640 --> 15:37.840
He landed in the techno trousers.

15:38.800 --> 15:41.280
There the wrong trousers!

15:41.920 --> 15:42.560
He cried.

15:43.600 --> 15:49.520
Then the trousers moved, but there was no control panel on the front of them to stop them.

15:50.480 --> 15:52.400
Where's the control panel?

15:52.960 --> 15:53.760
Cried Wallace.

15:54.400 --> 15:55.760
Stop them Gromit!

15:56.320 --> 15:58.640
Get me out of these trousers!

16:00.000 --> 16:04.400
But Gromit wasn't there, and the techno trousers didn't stop.

16:05.280 --> 16:10.800
They walked out of the front door and down the street with Wallace in them.

16:12.080 --> 16:15.120
Gromit looked at a sign in a shop window.

16:16.400 --> 16:18.480
Spare room to rent.

16:19.360 --> 16:20.800
Cheap, it said.

16:21.680 --> 16:23.920
Oh good, he thought.

16:24.560 --> 16:25.360
He read more.

16:26.240 --> 16:29.200
No dogs, the sign went on.

16:30.240 --> 16:32.720
Oh no, thought Gromit.

16:33.520 --> 16:37.200
Then he saw a picture of a chicken in the window.

16:38.240 --> 16:44.080
Help us to find this chicken, and you get one thousand pounds.

16:44.720 --> 16:45.520
Gromit read.

16:46.480 --> 16:48.240
He looked at the picture carefully.

16:49.040 --> 16:51.280
Did he know that chicken's face?

16:52.640 --> 16:56.800
Just then, Wallace ran past in the techno trousers.

16:57.360 --> 16:59.200
Help, Gromit!

16:59.600 --> 17:00.160
He cried.

17:00.720 --> 17:03.200
They're the wrong trousers!

17:04.400 --> 17:06.960
Gromit ran after his old friend.

17:08.240 --> 17:11.200
What's wrong with the techno trousers?

17:11.200 --> 17:11.680
He thought.

17:12.480 --> 17:17.760
And then, in the street in front of him, he saw the penguin.

17:19.120 --> 17:20.560
What's he got there?

17:21.200 --> 17:22.000
Thought Gromit.

17:22.800 --> 17:26.880
Quietly, he moved nearer, and then he saw.

17:27.840 --> 17:30.480
The penguin had the control panel.

17:31.440 --> 17:33.200
Now, Gromit understood.

17:34.000 --> 17:40.080
With the buttons and levers, the penguin could make the techno trousers move here,

17:40.080 --> 17:44.960
and there, up and down, and Wallace couldn't stop him.

17:46.160 --> 17:49.440
In the end, the techno trousers took Wallace home.

17:50.240 --> 17:52.080
He felt very tired by then.

17:53.040 --> 17:56.000
Because he couldn't get out of the techno trousers,

17:56.640 --> 18:00.720
he went to bed in them, and he went to sleep at once.

18:08.160 --> 18:09.120
Chapter 4.

18:09.840 --> 18:11.840
Watching and Waiting

18:16.480 --> 18:18.320
Gromit was in a coffee shop.

18:19.200 --> 18:22.320
He looked over his newspaper at the street,

18:22.320 --> 18:24.720
and saw the penguin walking past.

18:25.760 --> 18:31.200
He quickly put his newspaper down, left some money for his coffee on the table,

18:31.200 --> 18:33.920
and went out into the street after the penguin.

18:34.960 --> 18:38.560
Soon, the penguin stopped in front of a big, old building.

18:39.680 --> 18:41.440
What's he doing here?

18:42.160 --> 18:42.960
Thought Gromit.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.480
Suddenly, the penguin looked behind him.

18:47.200 --> 18:50.000
Gromit quickly hid behind some bins.

18:51.200 --> 18:55.200
Then the penguin looked back at the big, old building,

18:55.200 --> 18:58.560
and began writing lots of things down in a little book.

18:59.840 --> 19:05.760
Gromit got under an old box, and moved slowly nearer to the old building.

19:06.560 --> 19:08.320
But how could he see out now?

19:09.280 --> 19:09.760
Easy!

19:10.480 --> 19:15.280
He took out a little red knife, made a hole in the front of the box,

19:15.280 --> 19:17.040
and looked carefully through it.

19:18.560 --> 19:21.840
Now the penguin had a yellow tape measure in his hand.

19:22.800 --> 19:25.760
First he looked up at a high window over his head.

19:26.560 --> 19:29.840
After that, he made his tape measure very long,

19:29.840 --> 19:33.840
and put one end of it up on the ledge in front of the high window.

19:34.640 --> 19:38.080
And then, when the other end of the tape measure went up,

19:38.720 --> 19:43.200
the penguin shot up with it, and landed on the high window ledge.

19:44.160 --> 19:50.000
Up there, on the ledge, the penguin looked at the big window in front of him carefully.

19:50.880 --> 19:56.720
He measured it from left to right, and up and down,

19:57.440 --> 20:00.720
and he wrote lots more things down in his little book.

20:02.080 --> 20:06.160
When he finished writing, he put his book under his arm,

20:06.160 --> 20:09.680
and he put one end of the tape measure on the window ledge again.

20:10.400 --> 20:14.160
And then, when the other end of the tape measure went down,

20:14.160 --> 20:17.920
the penguin came down with it, and landed in the street.

20:18.880 --> 20:21.280
He began walking past Gromit's box.

20:22.320 --> 20:26.480
Suddenly, he stopped, and looked right at the box.

20:27.440 --> 20:30.560
Oh, no! He knows I'm in here!

20:31.120 --> 20:34.640
Thought Gromit, and he watched, and waited.

20:35.680 --> 20:39.200
But in the end, the penguin only looked at the box for a minute,

20:39.280 --> 20:40.240
and then walked on.

20:43.040 --> 20:46.880
Soon after that, Gromit came out from under the box,

20:46.880 --> 20:50.080
and ran back to 62 West Wallaby Street.

20:51.040 --> 20:56.560
He got there before the penguin, and at once went upstairs into his old room,

20:56.560 --> 20:58.080
now the penguin's room.

20:58.960 --> 21:02.560
He found something very interesting on the penguin's table.

21:03.440 --> 21:06.560
It was a picture of the big, old building,

21:07.120 --> 21:09.120
and all the different rooms in it.

21:10.000 --> 21:12.160
It was the town museum.

21:13.200 --> 21:17.440
And there, in the diamond room on the second floor,

21:17.440 --> 21:22.480
not far from the window, was a big, blue diamond.

21:23.680 --> 21:24.800
Of course!

21:25.600 --> 21:31.040
Thought Gromit, the penguin wants to get the blue diamond from the museum.

21:32.000 --> 21:36.240
Just then, he heard the back door open and close.

21:37.200 --> 21:40.000
Oh, no! The penguin's back!

21:40.560 --> 21:41.360
Thought Gromit.

21:41.920 --> 21:43.520
Where can I hide now?

21:44.640 --> 21:46.240
There was no time to run away.

21:47.120 --> 21:50.720
So in the end, Gromit hid in bed, next to Wallace.

21:51.600 --> 21:56.640
When he looked out, he saw the penguin bringing a big box into Wallace's room.

21:58.160 --> 22:00.400
Then the penguin put the box down.

22:01.040 --> 22:04.880
And Gromit saw the red glove on his head.

22:05.840 --> 22:09.920
At once he remembered the picture of the chicken in the shop window.

22:11.360 --> 22:13.440
So he's the chicken.

22:14.160 --> 22:16.720
Thought Gromit, and he hid again quickly.

22:18.000 --> 22:23.600
Now the penguin took a red helmet out of the box and put it on Wallace's head.

22:24.560 --> 22:27.040
Wallace slept happily through this.

22:28.000 --> 22:34.160
With the control panel of the techno trousers, the penguin made Wallace get out of bed,

22:34.160 --> 22:37.680
walk downstairs, and leave the house.

22:38.480 --> 22:40.880
Wallace slept through all this.

22:42.080 --> 22:46.560
And the penguin walked down the street after him to the town museum.

22:47.520 --> 22:53.040
At the same time, back in Wallace's room, the getting up machine began working.

22:53.920 --> 22:59.120
The head of the bed moved up, the door opened in the floor at its foot,

22:59.120 --> 23:01.520
and Gromit shot down through it.

23:02.160 --> 23:07.200
He landed in Wallace's brown trousers at the kitchen table,

23:07.200 --> 23:10.320
and there he got breakfast all over his face.

23:10.320 --> 23:20.400
Chapter 5, Hoops and Downs

23:27.440 --> 23:31.840
Wallace and the penguin walked through the dark streets to the museum,

23:32.720 --> 23:35.200
and Wallace didn't open his eyes once.

23:36.160 --> 23:41.520
When they arrived at the museum, the penguin moved some levers on the control panel.

23:42.160 --> 23:45.200
Then he jumped up on the techno trousers,

23:45.200 --> 23:49.280
and at once they began to walk up the wall of the museum.

23:50.160 --> 23:53.360
Soon the trousers arrived at the high window,

23:53.360 --> 23:57.600
and here the penguin jumped off and landed on the window ledge.

23:58.320 --> 24:02.880
He looked through the window at the beautiful blue diamond,

24:02.960 --> 24:05.760
and moved some more levers on the control panel.

24:06.880 --> 24:11.120
The techno trousers went higher up the wall with Wallace in them.

24:11.920 --> 24:14.160
At last they arrived at the roof.

24:15.040 --> 24:19.360
There they walked up, over and down an air vent,

24:20.000 --> 24:26.080
through the roof and down into the museum, and Wallace slept through it all.

24:27.680 --> 24:31.280
Now the penguin could see the techno trousers through the window.

24:32.240 --> 24:35.360
They came down through an air vent in the ceiling,

24:36.000 --> 24:39.040
walked over the ceiling tiles in the long room,

24:39.600 --> 24:42.960
and came nearer and nearer to the diamond room.

24:44.000 --> 24:48.880
But Wallace had long arms, and the penguin suddenly felt afraid.

24:49.600 --> 24:54.320
Those long arms could easily get in front of the alarm and make it ring,

24:55.120 --> 24:57.280
so he stopped the trousers for a time.

24:58.160 --> 25:01.840
In the end, Wallace moved his arms in his sleep,

25:02.320 --> 25:06.320
and the penguin quickly moved some levers on the control panel,

25:06.720 --> 25:08.560
and walked him past the alarm.

25:09.440 --> 25:11.760
Now the diamond was under him.

25:12.880 --> 25:15.920
Then the penguin hit a button on the control panel,

25:16.320 --> 25:19.360
and the red helmet on Wallace's head opened,

25:19.920 --> 25:24.240
and a steel machine claw came down out of it.

25:25.120 --> 25:31.520
After that, the penguin hit a different button and moved some of the levers on the control panel.

25:32.160 --> 25:39.920
The trousers moved, and the machine claw went down to the diamond and opened over it.

25:41.840 --> 25:48.080
Now the steel claw closed on the diamond, and the penguin hit some more buttons.

25:48.880 --> 25:56.000
The claw, with the diamond in it, slowly began to go up into Wallace's helmet.

25:56.960 --> 26:01.600
Then, suddenly, the diamond shot out of the claw.

26:02.240 --> 26:06.240
At once, the penguin moved the lever and hit a button.

26:06.800 --> 26:12.960
The steel claw shot down and closed on the diamond again before it hit the floor.

26:13.840 --> 26:21.760
Once again, the penguin hit some more buttons, and the claw moved up into the helmet with the diamond in it.

26:22.720 --> 26:24.720
Then, it happened.

26:25.120 --> 26:32.400
One of the ceiling tiles came off the ceiling, and with it came one of the feet of the techno trousers.

26:32.960 --> 26:41.280
At the same time, the helmet opened again, and the steel claw with the diamond in moved down in front of the alarm.

26:42.080 --> 26:50.080
The alarm began to ring, lights began to go on and off. Wallace opened his eyes.

26:50.880 --> 27:00.160
Where am I? What's that noise? He cried. At the same time, a big steel door closed in front of him.

27:01.040 --> 27:04.640
How could the penguin get the diamond out of the museum now?

27:05.600 --> 27:09.360
The air vent was in the long room behind the steel door.

27:10.080 --> 27:12.080
Gromit! Gromit!

27:13.200 --> 27:19.520
Cried Wallace. The penguin hit some buttons and moved some levers on the control panel.

27:20.240 --> 27:27.600
The techno trousers walked to the window and stood on it. At once, the window opened,

27:27.600 --> 27:34.240
and Wallace was out in the cold, standing on a high window looking up at the night sky.

27:35.280 --> 27:40.080
Now the trousers moved, and he could see the dark street under him.

27:41.040 --> 27:46.000
Get me down! Cried Wallace, help!

27:46.960 --> 27:54.960
Then the penguin jumped on Wallace's back, and the techno trousers quickly walked down the wall and ran away.

27:55.840 --> 28:04.160
You can't do this to me! Cried Wallace, stop it at once! I'm a good man, I am!

28:04.640 --> 28:25.040
The penguin took Wallace back to his room at 62 West Wallaby Street.

28:25.840 --> 28:33.440
There, Wallace took off the helmet and put it down. There too, the penguin took the red glove

28:33.440 --> 28:34.160
off his head.

28:35.360 --> 28:43.280
Oh, it's you, said Wallace, for he saw now it wasn't a chicken standing in front of him,

28:43.280 --> 28:51.280
but the penguin. Then he got angry. Get me out of these trousers this minute, he said.

28:52.240 --> 28:59.200
In answer, the penguin quickly put Wallace into a wardrobe and closed the door behind him.

28:59.280 --> 29:04.880
Help! Open this door at once! Cried Wallace in the wardrobe,

29:04.880 --> 29:11.280
and he knocked on the door angrily. The penguin took the diamond from the helmet,

29:11.280 --> 29:19.680
and put it in a bag. Then he walked to the door. But Gromit stood at the door. He was angry,

29:19.680 --> 29:26.560
and he had a big rolling pin in his hands. At once the penguin took out a big black gun.

29:27.440 --> 29:30.480
When he saw that, Gromit put his rolling pin down.

29:31.280 --> 29:37.920
Now the penguin opened the wardrobe door. Gromit got in with Wallace, and the penguin closed the

29:37.920 --> 29:45.040
door again. In the dark, Gromit began to put his hands down the front of the techno trousers.

29:46.160 --> 29:54.240
Oh, what are you doing? Cried Wallace, be careful, lad! Gromit put the end of a red wire

29:54.240 --> 30:00.800
on the end of a black wire, and the legs of the techno trousers began to move up and down,

30:01.440 --> 30:07.280
faster and faster. Soon the wardrobe broke away from the floor,

30:07.280 --> 30:12.160
and the trousers walked it out of the room with Wallace and Gromit in it.

30:13.200 --> 30:18.160
Where are we going? I can't see a thing! Cried Wallace.

30:19.120 --> 30:26.560
Then the wardrobe door opened and Gromit came out. The penguin jumped on the banister and went

30:26.560 --> 30:33.920
down it with the gun in his hand, and the diamond bag on his back. He landed on the front of Wallace's

30:33.920 --> 30:42.240
toy train. Get him, Gromit! Cried Wallace from in the wardrobe. Then the wardrobe began to go

30:42.320 --> 30:50.240
downstairs with Wallace in it. Gromit jumped up at once and caught the ceiling lamp. The penguin

30:50.240 --> 30:56.960
shot the lamp down from the ceiling, and Gromit landed near the back of Wallace's toy train

30:56.960 --> 31:02.480
with the lamp on his head. The train went off quickly down the track.

31:04.800 --> 31:11.840
The penguin was now behind the little blue train engine. He looked back and shot at Gromit

31:11.840 --> 31:19.840
again and again with his gun. But Gromit wasn't afraid. He had a lamp for a helmet on his head,

31:19.840 --> 31:26.800
and he wanted to catch the penguin. Suddenly he saw the train getting near the back door.

31:27.600 --> 31:35.200
Oh no! The penguin's going to get away, he thought. He hit a red button by the track,

31:35.280 --> 31:40.960
and the train went off to the left. It's okay, Gromit! Cried Wallace.

31:41.600 --> 31:48.320
He now stood on the last car at the end of the train on one leg of the techno trousers.

31:48.320 --> 31:55.360
I'm behind you, lad! He called. Now the penguin shot his gun at Wallace's feet,

31:55.360 --> 32:01.760
and Wallace's car jumped off the track and began to run on a new track next to the first.

32:02.640 --> 32:05.760
Stay there, Gromit! Everything's okay!

32:06.480 --> 32:11.920
Called Wallace. And he moved past his friend and got near the penguin.

32:12.800 --> 32:20.240
Give me that gun! Cried Wallace. He put out his hand and took the gun from the penguin.

32:20.240 --> 32:27.200
But suddenly the techno trousers hit the wall and Wallace came out of them, went through a hole

32:27.280 --> 32:34.640
in the wall and landed on a kitchen trolley. At once Gromit took the lamp off his head

32:34.640 --> 32:39.760
and began to move to the front of the train. Wallace went past him again.

32:40.960 --> 32:45.280
This time he was on his trolley, and he had a net in his hands.

32:45.920 --> 32:53.600
I'm going to get that penguin now, he cried. But then Wallace's net hit something on the wall,

32:53.600 --> 32:59.920
and this knocked him off the trolley. He landed back on the train. The penguin hit

32:59.920 --> 33:07.040
a little lever by the track. The engine, with the penguin on a car behind it, went off along

33:07.040 --> 33:13.680
one track. The back of the train, with Gromit on the first car and Wallace on the last car,

33:13.680 --> 33:21.840
went off along a different track. Suddenly Gromit had no more track in front of him.

33:22.560 --> 33:26.640
Oh, no! We're going to have an accident, he thought.

33:27.680 --> 33:34.320
Then he saw a box of new track on the floor, caught it, and quickly began to put the new

33:34.320 --> 33:41.680
track down in front of the train. So they went on, under the table, and into the next room.

33:42.800 --> 33:48.160
There Gromit's track ran over the penguin's track. At the back of the train,

33:48.240 --> 33:54.880
Wallace put out his hands to catch the penguin, but he only caught the little blue toy engine.

33:55.680 --> 34:01.200
Then the techno trousers walked in front of the penguin's car, and the penguin,

34:01.200 --> 34:09.280
with the diamond bag on his back, flew up, off the car, and into the kitchen. At the same time,

34:09.280 --> 34:16.720
Gromit hit the kitchen cupboard, and stopped suddenly. A milk bottle came down off the cupboard,

34:16.720 --> 34:23.280
and landed in his hand. A second later, the penguin landed in the milk bottle,

34:23.280 --> 34:26.640
and the diamond bag landed in Gromit's other hand.

34:27.680 --> 34:32.800
We did it, Gromit Land! We caught him!" cried Wallace.

34:34.160 --> 34:41.120
That afternoon they took the penguin to the police, and the police put him away in a very

34:41.120 --> 34:49.440
strong building for a very long time. That evening, Wallace and Gromit sat in the front room.

34:50.080 --> 34:56.560
They were friends again. Now we've got the thousand pounds from the police.

34:56.560 --> 35:02.320
We don't need to rent that spare room. Isn't that grand? said Wallace happily.

35:03.040 --> 35:09.360
Shall we have some cheese, Chuck? When Gromit got up to get the cheese,

35:09.360 --> 35:15.040
he looked out of the window at the old techno trousers, now in a bin in the street.

35:16.000 --> 35:24.160
And we don't need you, he thought happily. He went back into the front room with Wallace's

35:24.160 --> 35:32.080
cheese, and then sat down to read the newspaper. Out in the street, with no control panel to stop

35:32.080 --> 35:48.000
them, the techno trousers got up and walked off into the night.

